Context("Numeric");
#given
$l = 200;
$w = 75;
$t = 10;
$sx = -3;
$sy = 10;

#image scale
$imgScale = .2;

#image aspect ratio
$width = $imgScale*1978;
$height = $imgScale*1293;

#computation 
$theta = arctan($w/$l);
$c = ($sx + $sy)/2;
$r = sqrt(((($sx-$sy)/2)**2)+($tau**2));

$sigmaX = $c - $r*cos(2*$theta);
$sigmaY = $c + $r*cos(2*$theta);
$tau = $r*sin(2*$theta);

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image("UBC-SM-18-040.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A thin rectangular plate of dimensions [`[$l]`]x[`[$w]`]x[`[$t]`] [`mm`] is formed by welding two triangular plates. The plate supports the stresses shown in the diagram. Determine the normal and shear stresses acting perpendicular to the weld, and the normal and shear stresses acting parallel to the weld. 

[`\sigma_x=`] [____]{"$sigmaX"} [`MPa`]  
[`\sigma_y=`] [____]{"$sigmaY"} [`MPa`]  
[`\tau_{xy}=`] [____]{"$tau"} [`MPa`]  

END_PGML

